CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, December 2, 1961, pg. 14A, reads: "Story Hour - Mrs. Izetta Besley, seated in right foreground, has a captivating influence on this class of pre-school tots at the Wesley Center Day Nursery, as she relates the plight of 'Little Red Ridinghood' or 'The Three Bears.' Anxious listeners include (left to right) Levi Williams, Kevin Trower, Charlene Foggie, Richard Cobbs and Roderick Decree."
TitMainTitle: Izetta Woodson or Besley seating on child sized chair reading to children, from left: Levi Williams, Kevin Trower, Charlene Foggie, Richard Cobbs, and Roderick Decree, in Wesley Center AME Zion Church
